<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1870-07-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1870-07-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="42" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d42">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">THE UNITED STATES LEGATION IN PARIS TO THE
                            DEPARTMENT OF STATE.</note>
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 42.</note>
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. W. Hoffman</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Fish</persName>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Received 9.30 a. m. July 16,
                                1870.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-07-15"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 15, 1870.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Fish,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington:</hi></p>
                        <p>War is certain. Can I take Prussian subjects in France under our
                            protection? Have promised answer to-morrow.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>HOFFMAN.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>